description:
&lt;p&gt;The Directorate of Renal Medicine at Manchester Royal Infirmary is the Renal Centre for the Managed Clinical Network across the East Sector of Greater Manchester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Renal Technical Service provides technical support for departments deploying renal replacement therapies within the Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust and the East Sector Managed Clinical Network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working under supervision, the post holder will perform routine tasks within the broad range of work of The Renal Technical Services, to work always to a high standard of organisational and engineering competence within the operational policies and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where work is undertaken in the community, the post holder with support from the supervising Technologist, will exercise their knowledge and skills in determining the most appropriate course of action to ensure patient safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the high level of patient contact, a great degree of sensitivity and discretion will always be maintained and patient confidentiality respected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also be expected to attend a local college on a day release basis to further their electromechanical knowledge with a view to further progression within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameIan WildeJob titleTechnical Service ManagerEmail addressian.wilde@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 276 4333&lt;/p&gt;
